\backslash
rangle$ is $
\backslash
eta_{1} r_{i}$ while the prior probability of $
\backslash
vert %s_{i}
\backslash
rangle$ is $
\backslash
eta_{2} s_{i}$.
 We can define the normalized probabilities 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%
