\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%
\backslash
subsection{Lagrangian Optimization}
\end_layout

\end_inset

The remaining task is to determine the optimal distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 between the 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 subspaces, under the constraint of Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Nconstraint"

\end_inset

, i.e., to determine the optimal values of 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 as a function of the fixed 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to perform the optimization we employ the Lagrange multiplier method
 because it leads to more symmetric and easily tractable equations.
 To minimize the overall error rate 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{E}=\sum_{Pi=1}^{N}\frac{\omega_{i}}{2}(1-Q_{i}-\sqrt{(1-Q_{i})^{2}-(Q_{0,i}-Q_{i})^{2}})$
\end_inset

 subject to the constraint in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Qtot2"

\end_inset

 we form the function with one constraint 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda.$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
F=\sum_{i=1}^{N}\frac{\omega_{i}}{2}(1-Q_{i}-\sqrt{(1-Q_{i})^{2}-(Q_{0,i}-Q_{i})^{2}})+\lambda(Q-\sum_{i=1}^{N}\omega_{i}Q_{i})\ ,
\end{equation}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We vary the function 
\begin_inset Formula $F$
\end_inset

 treating 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 as the independent variables.
 Solving the resulting equations together with the constraint 
\begin_inset Formula $Q=\sum_{i=1}^{N}\omega_{i}Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 determines the value of the Lagrange multiplier which minimizes the error
 rate 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{e}=\sum_{i=1}^{N}\omega_{i}P_{e,i}.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before we present the results it will prove useful to introduce a hierarchy
 of the subspaces.
 So, in what follows we will assume 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
Q_{0,1}\geq Q_{0,2}\geq\ldots\geq Q_{0,N}\ ,\label{hierarchy}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

which generalizes the ordering used in the case of two subspaces in the
 previous section.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the optimal 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 can be written as  
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{eqnarray}
Q_{i}^{opt}=\left\{ \begin{array}{ll}
\frac{1-Q_{0,i}}{\sum_{i=1}^{k}\omega_{i}-\sum_{i=1}^{k}\omega_{i}Q_{0,i}}Q+\frac{Q_{0,i}\sum_{i=1}^{k}\omega_{i}-\sum_{i=1}^{k}\omega_{i}Q_{0,i}}{\sum_{i=1}^{k}\omega_{i}-\sum_{i=1}^{k}\omega_{i}Q_{0,i}} & \ \ \ \mbox{if \ensuremath{Q_{th}^{(k)}\leq Q\leq Q_{th}^{(k+1)}} and \ensuremath{i\leq k}}\ ,\\
0 & \ \ \ \mbox{if \ensuremath{i>k}}\ .
\end{array}\right.\label{Qiopt}
\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%
\backslash
begin{widetext}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%
\backslash
begin{eqnarray}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%    
\backslash
label{Qiopt}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%    Q_{}^{opt} = 
\backslash
left
\backslash
{ 
\backslash
begin{array}{ll}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

%    
\backslash
frac{Q}{ 
\backslash
omega_{1} } & 
\backslash
