\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results presented so far, in Sections III and IV, are valid if the parameter
s are such that in all subspaces we are in the POVM regime, i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 is in the unshaded region (region II) of Fig.
 1 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

.
 When the parameters are such that in some subspaces we are in the projective
 regime, i.e., 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 falls in the shaded regions of Fig.
 1 (regions I and III) for some 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 we have to modify the treatment to account for the fact that the error
 expression for the corresponding subspace, 
\begin_inset Formula $P_{e,i}$
\end_inset

, is no longer given by Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Pei2"

\end_inset

 but by 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol2"

\end_inset

.
 We will study this case in the next section.
\end_layout

