\begin_layout Section
Projective regime
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have seen in Section II for the single subspace case that the POVM solution
 is valid if the inconclusive rate is smaller than a boundary value, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q\leq Q_{b}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{b}$
\end_inset

 is given by Eq.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Qb"

\end_inset

.
 With an obvious generalization, the POVM solution holds in subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 if in that subspace 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}\leq Q_{b,i}$
\end_inset

 holds where the subspace boundary value is given by 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
Q_{{\rm b,i}}\equiv{2\eta_{1,i}\eta_{2,i}\sin^{2}\theta_{i}/(1-Q_{0,i})}.\label{Qbi}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

In Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Fig6"

\end_inset

 we plot 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{{\rm c,i}}$
\end_inset

 and
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $Q_{{\rm b,i}}$
\end_inset

 vs.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1}$
\end_inset

 together for a fixed overlap, 
\begin_inset Formula $\cos\theta=0.5$
\end_inset

 (
\begin_inset Formula $\theta=\pi/3$
\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement ht
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\series bold
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}$
\end_inset

 vs.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}$
\end_inset


\series default
 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout


\backslash
centering
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The two curves intersect at 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}=\eta_{1,i}^{(l)}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}=\eta_{1,i}^{(r)}$
\end_inset

, the same points as in Eq.
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "Qmax"

\end_inset

.
 The interval 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq\eta_{1,i}\leq1$
\end_inset

 is thus divided into three regions.
 In regions
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

I and
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

III, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{{\rm b,i}}<Q_{{\rm c,i}}$
\end_inset

 and the solution
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol1"

\end_inset

 is valid for 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq Q_{i}<Q_{{\rm b}}$
\end_inset

 only.
 In Region II, 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1,i}^{(l)}\leq\eta_{1,i}\leq\eta_{1,i}^{(r)}$
\end_inset

, we have 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{{\rm c,i}}=Q_{0,i}<Q_{{\rm b,i}}$
\end_inset

 and the solution 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "PeSol1"

\end_inset

 is valid for the entire 
\begin_inset Formula $0\leq Q_{i}\leq Q_{{\rm c,i}}$
\end_inset

 range.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{i}>Q_{b,i}$
\end_inset

 occurs in regions I and III and in the shaded areas the optimal FRIO measuremen
t is a standard projective measurement while in the unshaded area it is
 a POVM.
 We now illustrate the case when the FRIO measurement is a POVM in some
 and a Projection in other subspaces on a numerical example.
 We consider three subspaces with 
\begin_inset Formula $\eta_{1}=\eta_{2}$
\end_inset

 and the other parameters are listed in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "table1"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

