\begin_layout Standard
Subspace 1 has its maximum failure rate as 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{0,1}=\sqrt{2}/8\approx.17$
\end_inset

.
 For subspace 2, the maximum failure rate isn't 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{0,2}=\sqrt{6}/16\approx.15$
\end_inset

 because it fails one of the SSD conditions and instead 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{2}^{<}=7/32\approx.21$
\end_inset

, and for subspace 3 the maximum failure rate isn't 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{0,3}=3\sqrt{5}/16\approx.42$
\end_inset

, because it fails the other SSD condition and instead 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{3}^{>}=29/64\approx.45$
\end_inset

.
 The failure rate maximum 
\begin_inset Formula $Q^{MAX}=Q_{0,1}+Q_{2}^{<}+Q_{3}^{>}\approx.87$
\end_inset

 while 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{0}\approx.75$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\sum\omega_{i}=1$
\end_inset

 as it should.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
First elimination
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To find which subspace to discard first we find the critical Q's: 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{c}^{1}\approx.14$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{c}^{2}\approx.35$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{c}^{3}<0$
\end_inset

, so subspace 2 is discarded first when 
\begin_inset Formula $Q\approx.35$
\end_inset

.
 This means that 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{2}=0$
\end_inset

 when 
\begin_inset Formula $Q=Q_{c}^{2}$
\end_inset

 and we do not allow the value of 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{2}$
\end_inset

 to vary afterward.
 At 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{c}^{2}$
\end_inset

 we find the values of the other failure rates to be 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{1}\approx.06$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{3}\approx.29$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Second elimination
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It may be clear that 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{1}$
\end_inset

 will reach 0 first and indeed this is so.
 Before we find the second set of critical values we find our new constants
 as: 
\begin_inset Formula $\Lambda_{2}=\sum^{1,3}\omega_{i}=3/4$
\end_inset

; 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{2}=\sum^{1,3}Q_{0,i}\approx.6$
\end_inset

.
 Now the critical values read 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{c}^{(1)1}\approx.22$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q_{c}^{(1)3}<0$
\end_inset

 so when 
\begin_inset Formula $Q=Q_{c}^{(1)1}$
\end_inset

 we discard subspace 1 and reduce the optimization problem to the single
 subspace case, where 
\begin_inset Formula $Q^{(2)3}=Q$
\end_inset

.
 This process is depicted in Fig.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Fig7"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

